
- `Hospital` – manages permissions for examination types.
- `ExaminationType` – defines the different types of examinations.
- `TreatmentPlan` – associates with a problem and lists advised examination types.
- `Doctor` – affiliated with a hospital and prescribes treatments.
- `Patient` – visits a hospital and receives treatment.
- `Treatment` – represents an actual treatment applied to a patient.
- `Examination` – specific instance of an examination type performed.

---


@startuml
skinparam classAttributeStyle rectangle

class Hospital {
  +String name
  +Set<ExaminationType> allowedExaminations
  +applyPermission(ExaminationType)
}

class ExaminationType {
  +String typeName
  +Set<TreatmentPlan> relatedTreatmentPlans
}

class TreatmentPlan {
  +String problem
  +Set<ExaminationType> advisedExaminations
}

class Doctor {
  +String name
  +Hospital hospital
  +prescribeTreatment(Patient, Problem) : Treatment
}

class Patient {
  +String name
  +Hospital currentHospital
  +Treatment receivedTreatment
}

class Treatment {
  +Patient patient
  +Set<ExaminationType> advisedExaminations
  +Set<MedicalAction> medicalActions
}

class MedicalAction {
  +String description
}

class Examination {
  +ExaminationType type
  +Hospital performedAt
  +Patient patient
}

' Association between classes
Hospital "1" -- "0..*" ExaminationType : allows
ExaminationType "1" -- "0..*" TreatmentPlan : relates to
TreatmentPlan "1" -- "1" Doctor : used by
Doctor "1" -- "1" Hospital : belongs to
Doctor "1" -- "1" Patient : treats
Patient "1" -- "1" Treatment : has
Treatment "1" -- "0..*" Examination : includes
Treatment "1" -- "0..*" MedicalAction : includes
Examination "1" -- "1" Hospital : performed at
Examination "1" -- "1" Patient : belongs to

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:
- The diagram uses aggregation (`"1" -- "0..*"`) where appropriate (e.g., `Hospital` allows multiple `ExaminationType`s).
- Relationships such as `Doctor` prescribing `Treatment` are modeled as associations.
- `Examination` may be performed at a different `Hospital` than where the `Doctor` is affiliated.
- `Treatment` can include both advised `ExaminationType`s and additional `MedicalAction`s.

